1) chmod : change file permissions
    Options:
      - u : user/owner permissions
      - g : group permissions
      - o : other permissions
      - + : add permissions
      - - : remove permissions
      - = : set permissions
    Examples: chmod u+rwx file.txt => grants read, write and execute permissions to the owner of the file.

2) chown : change file ownership
    Example: chown user file.txt => changes the owner of file.txt to the specificed user

3) chgrp : change group ownership  
    Example: chgrp group file.txt => changes the group ownership of file.txt to the specified group.

4) umask : set default file permissions
    Example: umask 022 => sets the default file permissions to read and write for the owner and read-only
              for the group and others.
